---
description: Best practices for Next.js 15+ applications and routing
globs: apps/web/src/**/*.{ts,tsx}
---

- Use React Server Components by default, add `'use client'` only when necessary
- Minimize `use client`, `useEffect`, and `setState`; favor React Server Components (RSC)
- Limit `'use client'`:
  - Favor server components and Next.js SSR
  - Use only for Web API access in small components
  - Avoid for data fetching or state management
- Implement route handlers with Route Handler API instead of API routes
- Use next/image for optimized image loading
- Leverage server actions for form submissions
- Implement streaming with `loading.tsx` and suspense boundaries
- Cache responses with Route Cache Configuration
- Follow Next.js docs for Data Fetching, Rendering, and Routing
- Use `next-safe-action` for all server actions:
  - Implement type-safe server actions with proper validation.
  - Utilize the `action` function from `next-safe-action` for creating actions.
  - Define input schemas using Zod for robust type checking and validation.
